    "experiments": [
      {
        "experiment_id": 1,
        "reaction_type": "催化热解",
        "reaction_type_english": "Pyrolysis reaction",
        "description": "使用Ni/Hβ-沸石催化剂，在200-500°C的温度范围内，对盐角草种子进行催化热解和升级，以生产航空燃料范围的烃类。",
        "text_snippet": "Ni catalyst supported by the highly acidic nanocrystalline Hβ-zeolite was used to explore its hydrodeoxygenation capabilities on the pyrolytic bio-oil from Salicornia bigelovii (SB) at temperatures between 200 and 500 ◦C... The pyrolysis of the SB seeds was conducted in a horizontal tubular reactor... The first heating zone loaded with 1 g SB seeds... was ramped from 25 ◦C to 500 ◦C at 10 ◦C/min, maintaining an isothermal temperature at 200 ◦C, 300 ◦C, 400 ◦C and 500 ◦C for 10 min each... A catalytic bed of 1 g Ni/Ze packed in quartz wool... was kept in the second heating zone maintained at 500 ◦C throughout the experiment.",
        "reaction_type_classify": "Pyrolysis reaction"
      }
    ]
  },
